table_of_contents.title:
Most vesk in the Veskarium venerate Damoritosh the 
Conqueror, god of duty and war, and his army of battle 
saints. In life, the saints were mortal paragons who embodied 
vesk cultural values and attained divinity after earning 
Damoritosh's blessing; now they're worshipped alongside 
their deity. A typical vesk faces all of life's struggles armed 
with ideals of personal honor and strength, recognizing 
that not all conflicts occur on the battlefield. Many vesk 
find comfort in rigid systems of law, while others hold their 
personal sense of morality above all else—in either case, most 
vesk don't hesitate to fight for what they believe is right. 
Even while fighting, most vesk apply a code to their actions,
